            <img src="@Url.Content("/Content/images/index/icons-clock.png")" alt="" /><h4>Speaking Clock</h4>
            <p>Telstra’s 1194 time service (commonly known as ‘George the speaking clock’) has been running for decades providing traceable and accurate time for all Australians. Informatel took over the delivery of the vital 1194 service in 2002. We understand accuracy and mission critical services and time is no exception. We all rely on time. Informatel has designed with our partners the National Measurement Institute (regulators of the national standard of time measurement) a system without compromise.</p>
            <p>Informatel’s core time system is a redundant pair of Rubidium Atomic Clocks which are maintained within 500 microseconds of UTC (AUS). The traceability of this clock to the National Measurement Institute (NMI) and UTC (AUS) is established by continuous monitoring and recording of data.</p>
            <p>Informatel’s extensive infrastructure systems ensure that even during high demand periods such daylight savings start/end and New Years Eve, your call will always get through.</p>
            <br />
        </div>
